[5]
Date: 22 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Health Canada 21 Apr 2003 [edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/english/protection/warnings/sars/numbers.html>

Canadian SARS update 21 Apr 2003 5:00 PM
----------------------------------------
As of 21 Apr 2003, Health Canada has received reports of 316 probable or
suspect cases of SARS in Canada, with 14 deaths. To date, transmission has
been limited to specific transmission settings such as households,
hospitals, and specific community settings. The details of the cases to
date are as follows:
Ontario is reporting 135 probable and 124 suspect cases.
British Columbia is reporting 4 probable and 41 suspect cases.
New Brunswick is reporting 2 suspect cases.
Saskatchewan is reporting 1 suspect case.
Alberta is reporting 5 suspect cases.
Prince Edward Island is reporting 4 suspect cases.
So far, 129 people have been discharged from hospitals in Ontario. These
people were treated as suspect cases or as probable cases. These numbers
are accurate as of 1:00 pm. Eastern Daylight Saving Time, 21 Apr 2003. For
specific information on the provincial numbers, please contact the
appropriate provincial health department.
The World Health Organization has concluded that the coronavirus is the
cause of SARS. Health Canada's data are still unable to allow us to come to
that conclusion; however, national and international laboratory testing and
collaboration are ongoing.
[CDC added an interim travel advisory to Toronto, Ontario, Canada to the
website on 21 Apr 2003, which can be read at
<http://www.cdc.gov/travel/other/sars_can.htm>. - Mod.MPP]
